## Push Monitors

Push monitors allow services to report their own health status.

Example: Add this to a cron job or systemd timer:
```bash
curl -s "https://status.{{ target_domain | default('local') }}/api/push/YOUR_PUSH_TOKEN?status=up&msg=OK"
```

## Docker Container Monitoring

Uptime Kuma can monitor Docker containers directly:
1. Add a new monitor
2. Select "Docker Container" type
3. Enter the container name (e.g., `netdata`, `grafana`, etc.)

## Status Pages

Create public status pages at: Settings > Status Pages

Recommended status page groups:
- Infrastructure (DNS, Network, VPN)
- Applications (Web services, APIs)
- Monitoring (Grafana, Netdata, Loki)

